      "content": "yeah that makes sense. i'll check if remove_oldest is just popping from the vector without calling delete. \n\nbut what if the leak isn't in that specific function? we have other modules running in the background, like the CAN bus handler and the power management service. if none of my manual counters catch it, how would you suggest i narrow it down? i need a way to isolate which specific module is responsible for the creep without crashing the system or hogging the CPU.",
